node.text:
It was so special to put this package together for @camrynmary in honor of Suicide Prevention Month, and watching her unbox it is even more special 🥺 Thank you Camryn for being a proud suicide prevention advocate. We are so lucky to have you in this community because we know that together we can help stop suicide. 

Hope every single reminder we included supports you when you need it. 💙

This month, 100% of the profits from our ‘Together We Can Help Stop Suicide’ collection goes to @afspnational ✨🤍

node.text:
Today is #WorldSuicidePreventionDay 🌎

💙 We have partnered with @afspnational on our month-long campaign which is centered around encouraging all communities to become more comfortable talking about suicide and to check-in on loved ones and their mental health. 

We will continue to share our co-created conversation guides throughout the month because conversations around suicide can be challenging and scary. We want to support all communities in these conversations because you don’t have to do it alone. 🦋

Together we can help #stopsuicide

node.text:
It can be hard to know what to say when someone shares that they’ve been thinking about suicide 💔

Recognize that someone opening up to you in this way is a positive thing. It’s an opportunity to help someone feel seen and supported in a time of need. 🌈

We have compiled some examples of how to respond with compassion and care. 

✨ Know that this is not an easy conversation for anyone to have and there is no perfect way to have it!

Save this conversation guide in case you ever need support in knowing how to respond. 💙

🦋 In honor of Suicide Prevention Week, we will be sharing conversation guides that we have co-created with @afspnational here on Instagram all week long. ✨

Together we can help #StopSuicide

🦋 In honor of Suicide Prevention Week, we will be sharing conversation guides that we have co-created with @afspnational here on Instagram all week long. 💙

💞 Our hope is to support our community in having these difficult conversations. 

🧠 While it has become increasingly more common to talk about mental health, particularly this past year, the topic of suicide – when it comes up – is still scary for many people to think about, let alone say the word: Suicide.

🌧 Some may be afraid that by asking someone if they’re having thoughts of suicide, it will put the idea in their head, or perhaps push them to take their own life. (Which research shows is not true.)

🌈 We see this as an opportunity to deepen the conversation. We all have mental health. It’s time we take the next step, checking in on one another's mental health, and if we need it, find help together.

🌈 GOING TO THERAPY IS COOL IS BACK 😊🌈

Therapy builds resilience and it becomes a place to acknowledge how much strength it took to grow through what you have experienced in your life. ⛅️

Therapy, as a self-care practice, has the ability to save lives. It's a brave space to notice, recognize, and let go of judgement alongside a trained professional who will navigate the healing journey with you. 🌞

So, yeah... I guess you can tell that we think therapy is pretty cool.
